This patch modifies BubblewrapLauncher.cpp in WPE WebKit 2.50.5 for SFOS/Android
kernel 4.14 compatibility. Apply to:
  Source/WebKit/UIProcess/Launcher/glib/BubblewrapLauncher.cpp

Two issues fixed:

1. pivot_root(2) is not supported inside user namespaces on Android kernel 4.14.
   The normal WPE sandbox creates a new minimal tmpfs root and calls pivot_root,
   which fails on this kernel even for root. Workaround: use --dev-bind / / to
   bind the entire host filesystem instead of selective bind-mounts. This gives
   up filesystem isolation but keeps seccomp + namespace separation.

   Do NOT use --dev /dev after --dev-bind / / — it would mount a minimal
   devtmpfs that hides GPU device nodes (/dev/kgsl-3d0, /dev/dri, /dev/ion)
   that WPEWebProcess needs to render web content.

2. /.flatpak-info cannot be written into the sandbox root because SFOS root fs
   is read-only. Since SFOS does not use desktop portals, skip flatpak-info
   creation entirely by setting flatpakInfoFd = -1.

--- BubblewrapLauncher.cpp.orig
+++ BubblewrapLauncher.cpp
@@ sandboxArgs initialization (search for "Vector<CString> sandboxArgs")
 Replace the entire sandboxArgs initialization block with:

     // SFOS/Android kernel 4.14 does not support pivot_root(2) inside a user
     // namespace, so we cannot create a minimal new root via the normal
     // selective bind-mount approach.  Instead, bind the whole host filesystem
     // read-write and rely on seccomp + namespace isolation for security.
     Vector<CString> sandboxArgs = {
         "--unshare-uts",

         "--dev-bind", "/", "/",
         // Do NOT use "--dev /dev" here: it would mount a minimal devtmpfs that
         // hides GPU device nodes (/dev/kgsl-3d0, /dev/dri, /dev/ion, etc.)
         // that WPEWebProcess needs to render.  The host /dev is already
         // available via --dev-bind / / above.
         "--proc", "/proc",
         "--tmpfs", "/tmp",
         "--unsetenv", "TMPDIR",
         "--dir", runDir,
         "--setenv", "XDG_RUNTIME_DIR", runDir,
     };

@@ flatpakInfoFd creation (search for "createFlatpakInfo")
 Set flatpakInfoFd = -1 unconditionally to skip /.flatpak-info creation:

     // SFOS root filesystem is read-only; skip flatpak-info (not needed anyway).
     int flatpakInfoFd = -1;
